# SEO Optimization Requirements

All pages in this Next.js application must be optimized for search engines with proper metadata and structured data.

## Required SEO Elements

### 1. Metadata Export

Every page must export a `metadata` object or use `generateMetadata` function for dynamic metadata. This includes:

- **title**: Page title (required)
- **description**: Meta description (required, 120-160 characters)
- **openGraph**: Open Graph tags for social sharing
- **twitter**: Twitter Card metadata
- **keywords**: Relevant keywords (optional but recommended)

### 2. Schema Markup (JSON-LD)

All pages must include structured data using JSON-LD format. Common schema types:
- **WebSite**: For homepage
- **WebPage**: For standard pages
- **CollectionPage**: For listing pages (e.g., dashboard with decks)
- **ItemList**: For list-based content

### 3. Implementation Pattern

#### Static Metadata (Simple Pages)

```typescript
import type { Metadata } from "next";

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title | FlashyCardy",
  description: "A clear, concise description of the page (120-160 characters)",
  keywords: ["keyword1", "keyword2", "keyword3"],
  openGraph: {
    title: "Page Title | FlashyCardy",
    description: "A clear, concise description of the page",
    type: "website",
    siteName: "FlashyCardy",
  },
  twitter: {
    card: "summary_large_image",
    title: "Page Title | FlashyCardy",
    description: "A clear, concise description of the page",
  },
};
```

#### Dynamic Metadata (Pages with Dynamic Content)

```typescript
import type { Metadata } from "next";

export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  // Fetch dynamic data
  const data = await fetchData(params.id);
  
  return {
    title: `${data.title} | FlashyCardy`,
    description: data.description || "Default description",
    openGraph: {
      title: `${data.title} | FlashyCardy`,
      description: data.description,
      type: "website",
    },
  };
}
```

#### Schema Markup Component

Create a reusable component for schema markup:

```typescript
// components/schema-markup.tsx
export function SchemaMarkup({ schema }: { schema: object }) {
  return (
    <script
      type="application/ld+json"
      dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(schema) }}
    />
  );
}
```

#### Usage in Pages

```typescript
import { SchemaMarkup } from "@/components/schema-markup";

export default function Page() {
  const schema = {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "Page Title",
    "description": "Page description",
    "url": "https://yourdomain.com/page",
  };

  return (
    <>
      <SchemaMarkup schema={schema} />
      {/* Page content */}
    </>
  );
}
```

## SEO Checklist

Before marking a page as complete, ensure:

- [ ] `metadata` export or `generateMetadata` function is present
- [ ] Title includes site name (e.g., "Page Title | FlashyCardy")
- [ ] Description is 120-160 characters and accurately describes the page
- [ ] Open Graph tags are included for social sharing
- [ ] Twitter Card metadata is included
- [ ] Appropriate JSON-LD schema markup is added
- [ ] Schema type matches the page content (WebPage, CollectionPage, etc.)
- [ ] All URLs in schema are absolute (include full domain)
- [ ] Keywords are relevant and not overused

